  "body": "Sometimes Dapps request to sign transactions with crazy-long amounts. Usually, it's not important for the user to see the whole amount, however, there might be edge-cases when that is important.\n\n**For numbers with a lot of digits after the decimal point e.g `4.594095049504905`**\n\n* Round the amount in the title and leave just 6 digits after the decimal point;\n* Do the same in the `Amount` field;\n\n![](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3115606/73080967-c7406b80-3ed7-11ea-91d1-37c6acb34b33.png)\n\n*_For huge numbers (starting with tens of billions or `10 000 000 000`) *_\n\n* Show the approximate value in the title, the Instagram way (100Ðš, 2M, 4T) (e.g `Authorize ~3T SNT`);\n* Show only the first 6 digits + `...` in `Amount` field;\n\n![](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3115606/73081104-12f31500-3ed8-11ea-8e25-67cff02ef61d.png)\n\n**Both**\n\n* Round the network fee and leave just 6 digits after the decimal point;\n* For the USD value, leave only 2 digits after the decimal point;\n* Add a `>` icon and make tappable the amount field, if the amount consists of more than 8 digits and show he whole amount in a separate bottom sheet;\n\nFigma: https://www.figma.com/file/XUehMnhyD1FGcWzvGz6SXqvh/Wallet?node-id=3864%3A33253",
